gradProgram.description: The 2018 B.C. Certificate of Graduation or "Dogwood Diploma" program.

specialCaseList.label: NC
specialCaseList.description: Not Completed. Student attempted to write but did not complete enough of the Provincial Graduation Assessment to obtain a proficiency score.

specialCaseList.label: DSQ
specialCaseList.description: Disqualified. Student is believed to have breached one or more rules during a Provincial Graduation Assessment.

specialCaseList.label: MET
specialCaseList.description: The Assessment requirement has been met by a Provincial Exam.

specialCaseList.label: AEG
specialCaseList.description: Aegrotat Standing. The student has been granted exemption from writing a Provincial Graduation Assessment due to unpredictable circumstances that render a student unable to write an assessment, even at a future session.

algorithmRuleCode.label: Incomplete Courses
algorithmRuleCode.description: Checks if the course session date has passed (e.g., earlier than today - YYYYMM) and no final result or special case exists.

algorithmRuleCode.label: Incomplete Assessments
algorithmRuleCode.description: Checks if the assessment session date has passed (e.g., earlier than today - YYYMM) and no final result or special case exists

algorithmRuleCode.label: Course Registrations
algorithmRuleCode.description: Checks if the course session date is current or future dated (e.g., from today YYYYMM) or later) and no final result or special case exists

algorithmRuleCode.label: Assessment Registrations
algorithmRuleCode.description: Checks if the assessment date is current or future dated (e.g., from today YYYYMM) or later) and no final result or special case exists

algorithmRuleCode.label: Registration Duplicate Course
algorithmRuleCode.description: Checks if there are duplicate in progress courses (i.e., same course code and course level)

algorithmRuleCode.label: Registration Duplicate Assessment
algorithmRuleCode.description: Checks if there are duplicate in progress assessments (i.e. same assessment code)

algorithmRuleCode.label: Registration Failed Course
algorithmRuleCode.description: Checks letter grade table to determine when an interim letter grade or special case is not considered a successful completion

algorithmRuleCode.label: Failed Courses
algorithmRuleCode.description: Checks letter grade table to determine whether a letter grade or special case is not considered a successful completion

algorithmRuleCode.label: Failed Assessments
algorithmRuleCode.description: Checks Assessment Special case codes table to determine whether a special case is not considered a successful completion

algorithmRuleCode.label: Excluded courses after Program Expiry Date
algorithmRuleCode.description: If course session date is after the Program Expiry Date (e.g., graduation program closed date), excludes the course from the graduation algorithm

algorithmRuleCode.label: Duplicate Courses
algorithmRuleCode.description: If duplicate course code and course level is found, uses the course with the highest number of credits, then highest final %, then earliest session date

algorithmRuleCode.label: Duplicate Assessments
algorithmRuleCode.description: If duplicate assessment code, uses the assessment with the highest proficiency score, then special case (AEG, or Exempt/MET), then earliest session.

algorithmRuleCode.label: Career Preparation Courses
algorithmRuleCode.description: Excludes Career Preparation (e.g., course code starts with CP) courses from meeting any Requirement Type on the 2004 or 2018 program

algorithmRuleCode.label: Locally Developed Courses
algorithmRuleCode.description: Excludes Locally Developed (e.g., course code starts with X) courses from meeting any Requirement Type on the 1950 program

algorithmRuleCode.label: Restricted Courses
algorithmRuleCode.description: If a course is restricted against another course, uses the course with the highest number of credits, then highest final %, then earliest session date

algorithmRuleCode.label: Minimum Credits
algorithmRuleCode.description: Checks if student earned a minimum of 16 credits (of the 80 total credits needed for graduation) in eligible courses at the Grade 12 level

algorithmRuleCode.label: Match Credits
algorithmRuleCode.description: Checks if student earned a minimum of 4-credits in one or more eligible courses for a required subject area (i.e., courses listed under the applicable Rule #)

algorithmRuleCode.label: Assessments Match Credits
algorithmRuleCode.description: Checks if student has met Assessment requirements for their main program (i.e., those listed under the applicable rule number)

algorithmRuleCode.label: Minimum Elective Credits
algorithmRuleCode.description: Checks if student earned a minimum of 28 elective credits

algorithmRuleCode.label: FI - Match Credits
algorithmRuleCode.description: Checks if student earned a minimum of 4-credits in one or more eligible courses for a required French Immersion subject area (i.e., courses listed under the applicable Rule #)

algorithmRuleCode.label: FI - Assessments Match Credits
algorithmRuleCode.description: Checks if student has met Assessment requirements for the French Immersion program (i.e., those listed under the applicable rule number)

algorithmRuleCode.label: Assessment Equivalency
algorithmRuleCode.description: Checks for eligible, successfully completed courses with a written provincial exam to meet a Graduation Assessment requirement

algorithmRuleCode.label: FI - Minimum Elective Credits
algorithmRuleCode.description: Checks if student earned a minimum of 12 elective credits from courses taught in French, and if 4 of these credits are at the grade 11 or 12 level

algorithmRuleCode.label: CP - Match Credits
algorithmRuleCode.description: Checks if a student earned a minimum of 3 credits in an eligible work experience course

algorithmRuleCode.label: No Rule for School Reported Optional Programs
algorithmRuleCode.description: Identifies school reported Optional Programs where the only requirement is that the school has reported student participation in an optional program

algorithmRuleCode.label: All Requirements Met
algorithmRuleCode.description: Checks if all associated requirements for a main program are met or not met and determines the program completion status
